snippet.textDisplay: I know Junaid Jamshed turned his back to music as he closer to religion and Ali Haider among a few others have had their doubts but the copious tears I've shed at my own insignificance and the blessedness of being a follower of Muhammad SAW that has enveloped the depth of my being every time I hear this tells me music can be a way to uncover the pure, uncorrupted soul one is born with under the layers of worldly desires and corruption. May Allah bless Atif and the team behind this soul stirring soaring piece and give them ajar for making a sinner like me repent at my actions.
